## Scope Management — DO NOT TRY TO BUILD EVERYTHING

SPEC.md may list 30+ expected files. **You do NOT need to create all of them.** Focus on:
1. The CORE functionality (the main algorithm/technique from the paper)
2. A working CLI entry point (main.go / cli.py / index.ts)
3. At least 3 test files that PASS
4. Working `make test`

A product with 5 solid files that compiles and passes tests is infinitely better than 30 skeleton files that crash on import.

